node.title: Woman, 75, dies when car swept off road in 'treacherous' flash flooding in Brisbane
node.description: A member of the public alerted police after seeing aÂ woman's car enter floodwaters across a Pullenvale road and get swept away.
node.content:
["A 75-year-old woman has died in floodwaters in Brisbane's outer west, after her car was swept off the road.", "Regional Duty Officer Inspector Daniel Bragg said\u00a0police were called to Lancing Street in Pullenvale about 4:40pm yesterday by a member of the public, who had seen the woman's car enter floodwaters and get washed away.", "The rapidly moving waters were described as \"treacherous\" by police, with\u00a0Inspector Bragg saying officers were not able to find the car for three hours.", "Swift water crews were called in.", "\"Because of the rapidly rising water, and the speed at which the water was flowing, it took a considerable amount of time, several hours to actually locate the vehicle,\" he said.", "Inspector Bragg said a tree branch had snapped off and fallen on top of the car which made the rescue effort even more difficult.", "The woman, from the Brisbane suburb of Taringa,\u00a0was found dead inside the car.", "", "
Water was still over roads in Pullenvale this morning.
", "Her car had been fully submerged and needed to be towed out from waters.", "\"We've got [the] forensic crash [investigations unit] here. [They will]\u00a0be examining all of the circumstances surrounding this to work out exactly what's happened here,\" he said.", "\"This is an absolutely tragic incident.\"", "The woman's death is the third flood-related death in a month.", "Inspector Bragg said that, if there was\u00a0flood waters across roads, drivers should never attempt to cross.", "\"You need to drive with extreme caution. If it is flooded, don't drive through it because things like this can unfold so quickly and, before you know it, things are out of your control,\" he said."]
